### standard-governance.mdx
Describes how the ARAF standard is maintained. Current model: founder-led governance under Venture Bench Pty Ltd. Four governance principles: version discipline, public transparency, methodological consistency, institutional usability. Scope covers version publication, methodology maintenance, interpretive clarification, version history, and public documentation stewardship. Explicitly states that standard governance does not constitute assessor accreditation, certification issuance, or statutory authority. Future governance may include technical contributors, institutional advisory group, certification partners, accredited assessors, and a formal amendment process.

